Kenya Sugar Millers Increase Payments Amid Shortage, Business Daily Says

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-08-17T04:59:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/kenya-sugar-millers-increase-payments-amid-shortage-business-daily-says.html
Kenyan sugar millers including
Mumias Sugar Co. are paying farmers an average of 9.2 percent
more for their cane amid a shortage of the sweetener, Business
Daily reported.  Mumias increased its payments to growers to 3,475 shillings
($37.27) per metric ton of cane from 3,200 shillings previously,
the Nairobi-based newspaper said, citing Mumias Finance Director
Peter Kebati. It didnâ€™t say what period the increase was for.  To contact the reporter on this story:
